Arsonists stormed the home of Nyakach MP Aduma Owuor Saturday night and torched his vehicle and a store.Kisumu County police boss Joseph Keitany said they had launched investigations into the mid-night incident."They burnt the MPs Pajero [car] and we are yet to confirm the reasons behind the attack," Mr Keitany said.The police boss said they were investigating whether the incident could have been a revenge attack following last week's suicide of Nyabondo Primary School headteacher George Omondi.Mr Omondi is said to have left a suicide note allegedly linking the MP and other officials to his frustrations leading to his death.In November 2013, gangsters raided the MP s home, bludgeoned his parents to death and set their house ablaze.Less than a week after his parents were brutally murdered, Mr Owuor reported to the police that he had received death threats. email print email print Gangsters raided the home of Nyakach MP Aduma Owuor, bludgeoned his parents to death and set their house ablaze.Kenya is lobbying against the planned agreement between US and 12 Asian states for fear of losingPeres will be buried next to Rabin, who was assassinated in 1995 by a Jewish extremist opposed to